block content 
    h1.bd-title#content Parallax
    p.bd-lead paroller.js is a lightweight jQuery plugin that enables parallax scrolling effect on selected elements.
    ul
        li You can use it on elements with background property or on any other element.
        li While scrolling elements can move: vertical, horizontal.
        li Manipulated through html data-* attributes or jQuery options.
        li Mobile ready.
        li Easy to use.
    
    .mt-5#usage
        h2 Usage
        p To enable parallax scrolling effect you can use 
            code data-paroller-* 
            | attributes on selected elements or set 
            strong values via jQuery. 
            code 'factor' 
            | sets speed and distance of element's parallax effect on scroll.
        
        +alert-info("Since <code>'factor'</code> is multiplier it <strong>must be set for paroller.js to have parallax effect.</strong>") 
        figure.highlight
            pre
                code.js.
                    .paroller Awesome element with parallax effect

                    // initialize paroller.js and set attributes for selected elements
                    $(".paroller, [data-paroller-factor]").paroller({
                        factor: 0.3,            // multiplier for scrolling speed and offset
                        factorXs: 0.1,           // multiplier for scrolling speed and offset
                        type: 'foreground',     // background, foreground
                        direction: 'horizontal' // vertical, horizontal
                    });
        
        figure.highlight
            pre
                code.js.
                    div(data-paroller-factor="-0.1"
                        data-paroller-factor-xs="0.1"
                        data-paroller-type="foreground"
                        data-paroller-direction="vertical")
                        | Awesome element with parallax effect

                    // initialize paroller.js
                    $("[data-paroller-factor]").paroller();

